15	Looker Recreation	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Per school: # of students absent per day", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Should be able to use my current data pull, but with an addition to make things easier:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Whether code is absent or not.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	7	2026-02-25 16:41:59.110886	2026-03-12 12:30:52.809065
7	Next Steps	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The next steps for this project will be the major rebuild. I think the big portion of the change will be the page layout and how all of that can work, potentially making for a more simplified routing and updating layout. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The rebuild will also need to include a nicely cleaned up database structure. I’ll want to sit down with the current structure and get my head around it.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	2	2026-02-02 00:56:56.325879	2026-02-03 14:32:46.443536
23	Collections and Dashboard ideas	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Illinois Report Card", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "We can make a collection of dashboards that will give overviews of the metrics involved with the Illinois Report Card.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I’ve pulled the collection of data they are looking at, so we can go through each segment and create a look. We can also provide a bit of diving analytics for each section as well.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Segments:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Baseline info - Counts and Enrollment", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Enrollment", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Demographic Breakdown", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Mobility Rates", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Class Sizes", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Attendance", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Chronic Absenteeism", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Chronic Truancy", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Teacher Info", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Demographic Breakdown", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Survey Info", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "5 Essentials", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "CRDC", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Attendance", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Tackle the back list of things on the giant post it.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Chronic Absenteeism and Truancy", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Percentage of building/district", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Counts over time", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	7	2026-03-12 15:45:42.436524	2026-03-12 18:44:32.782176
17	Mac Mini Setup	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Key Settings", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Energy", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Prevent automatic sleeping = on", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Wake for network access = on", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Start up automatically after power failure = on", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Lock Screen", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Turn display off when inactive = Never", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Require password = Never", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Wallpaper", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Start Screen Saver = Never (in extra menu)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Login Password", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Automatically login after restart = on", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	8	2026-03-05 04:08:02.916741	2026-03-05 04:54:30.496345
24	SQL Insights	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "We have a unique opportunity to capture and present data much more efficiently. Here’s an example of an improvement I can make:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I’m trying to calculate the 180 day rolling window information within Metabase itself. While it does seem possible that this would work, this creates a large amount of calculations to be executed during the live dashboard. We can circumvent this by “prepossessing” the needed indicators as a simple true/false indicators and count that.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Attendance", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "This will use a date range and pull the attendance data for that range. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "xml"}, "content": [{"text": "WITH ALLENROLLMENTS AS (\\n    SELECT\\n        students.id AS studentid,\\n        students.dcid,\\n        students.student_number,\\n        students.schoolid,\\n        students.entrydate,\\n        students.exitdate,\\n        students.grade_level,\\n        students.ethnicity\\n    FROM\\n        students\\n    UNION\\n    ALL\\n    SELECT\\n        reenrollments.studentid,\\n        students.dcid,\\n        students.student_number,\\n        reenrollments.schoolid,\\n        reenrollments.entrydate,\\n        reenrollments.exitdate,\\n        reenrollments.grade_level,\\n        students.ethnicity\\n    FROM\\n        reenrollments\\n        JOIN students ON reenrollments.studentid = students.id\\n),\\nHISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS AS (\\n    SELECT\\n        ALLENROLLMENTS.dcid,\\n        ALLENROLLMENTS.grade_level,\\n        schools.name AS school,\\n        CASE\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.lii) = '0' THEN 'No'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.lii) = '1' THEN 'Yes'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.lii) IS NULL THEN 'No'\\n            ELSE to_char(s_il_stu_x.lii)\\n        END AS low_income,\\n        CASE\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_plan504_x.participant) = '0' THEN 'No'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_plan504_x.participant) = '1' THEN 'Yes'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_plan504_x.participant) IS NULL THEN 'No'\\n            ELSE to_char(s_il_stu_plan504_x.participant)\\n        END AS has_504,\\n        CASE\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.iep) = '0' THEN 'No'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.iep) = '1' THEN 'Yes'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.iep) IS NULL THEN 'No'\\n            ELSE to_char(s_il_stu_x.iep)\\n        END AS has_iep,\\n        CASE\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.LEP) = '0' THEN 'No'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.LEP) = '1' THEN 'Yes'\\n            WHEN to_char(s_il_stu_x.LEP) IS NULL THEN 'No'\\n            ELSE to_char(s_il_stu_x.LEP)\\n        END AS has_lep,\\n        (\\n            SELECT\\n                gen.name\\n            FROM\\n                gen gen\\n            WHERE\\n                gen.cat = 'ethnicity'\\n                AND gen.value = ALLENROLLMENTS.ethnicity\\n        ) AS ethnicity,\\n        calendar_day.date_value AS att_date,\\n        COALESCE(attendance_code.att_code, 'Present') AS att_code,\\n        COALESCE(\\n            CAST(attendance_code.description AS VARCHAR2(100)),\\n            'Present'\\n        ) AS att_description,\\n        NVL(attendance_code.presence_status_cd, 'Present') AS status,\\n        ada.membershipvalue AS membership_value,\\n        CASE \\n            WHEN NVL(attendance_code.presence_status_cd, 'Present') = 'Present' \\n                AND ada.attendancevalue = 0 THEN NULL \\n            ELSE ada.attendancevalue \\n        END AS attendance_value,\\n        SUM(\\n            CASE\\n                WHEN NVL(attendance_code.presence_status_cd, 'Present') = 'Present'\\n                    AND ada.attendancevalue = 0 THEN 0\\n                WHEN ada.attendancevalue = 0 THEN 1\\n                WHEN ada.attendancevalue = 0.5 THEN 0.5\\n                ELSE 0\\n            END\\n        ) OVER (\\n            PARTITION BY ALLENROLLMENTS.studentid\\n            ORDER BY\\n                calendar_day.date_value ROWS BETWEEN 179 PRECEDING\\n                    AND CURRENT ROW\\n        ) AS absent_count_180,\\n        SUM(\\n            CASE\\n                WHEN NVL(attendance_code.presence_status_cd, 'Present') = 'Present'\\n                    AND ada.attendancevalue = 0 THEN 0\\n                WHEN ada.attendancevalue = 0\\n                    AND attendance_code.att_code IN ('AUX', 'OSS')\\n                    AND ALLENROLLMENTS.grade_level >= 1 THEN 1\\n                ELSE 0\\n            END\\n        ) OVER (\\n            PARTITION BY ALLENROLLMENTS.studentid\\n            ORDER BY\\n                calendar_day.date_value ROWS BETWEEN 179 PRECEDING\\n                    AND CURRENT ROW\\n        ) AS truant_count_180\\n    FROM\\n        (\\n            SELECT\\n                *\\n            FROM\\n                ALLENROLLMENTS\\n        ) ALLENROLLMENTS\\n        INNER JOIN schools ON ALLENROLLMENTS.schoolid = schools.school_number\\n        INNER JOIN calendar_day ON ALLENROLLMENTS.schoolid = calendar_day.schoolid\\n            AND calendar_day.date_value >= ALLENROLLMENTS.entrydate\\n            AND calendar_day.date_value < ALLENROLLMENTS.exitdate\\n            AND calendar_day.insession = 1\\n        LEFT JOIN attendance ON attendance.studentid = ALLENROLLMENTS.studentid\\n            AND attendance.att_date = calendar_day.date_value\\n        LEFT JOIN attendance_code ON attendance.attendance_codeid = attendance_code.id\\n        LEFT JOIN s_il_stu_x ON ALLENROLLMENTS.dcid = s_il_stu_x.studentsdcid\\n        LEFT JOIN s_il_stu_plan504_x ON ALLENROLLMENTS.dcid = s_il_stu_plan504_x.studentsdcid\\n        LEFT JOIN ps_adaadm_defaults_all ada ON ALLENROLLMENTS.studentid = ada.studentid\\n            AND calendar_day.date_value = ada.calendardate\\n    WHERE\\n        calendar_day.date_value <= TO_DATE(:exitdate, 'MM/DD/YYYY')\\n        AND (\\n            (\\n                schools.name = 'Minooka Primary Center'\\n                AND (\\n                    attendance.att_mode_code = 'ATT_ModeMeeting'\\n                    OR attendance.att_mode_code IS NULL\\n                )\\n            )\\n            OR (\\n                attendance.att_mode_code = 'ATT_ModeDaily'\\n                OR attendance.att_mode_code IS NULL\\n            )\\n        )\\n        AND (\\n            s_il_stu_x.rcdts_serving_school IS NULL\\n            OR s_il_stu_x.rcdts_serving_school IN (\\n                '240322010042001',\\n                '240322010041002',\\n                '240322010043001',\\n                '240322010042003',\\n                '240322010042002',\\n                '240322010042005',\\n                '240322010042004'\\n            )\\n        )\\n) \\n\\nSELECT\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.dcid,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.grade_level,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.school,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.low_income,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.has_504,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.has_iep,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.has_lep,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.ethnicity,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.att_date,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.att_code,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.att_description,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.status,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.membership_value,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.attendance_value,\\n    CASE\\n        WHEN HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.absent_count_180 >= 18 THEN 'Yes'\\n        ELSE 'No'\\n    END AS is_chronically_absent_on_day,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.absent_count_180,\\n    CASE\\n        WHEN HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.truant_count_180 >= 9 THEN 'Yes'\\n        ELSE 'No'\\n    END AS is_chronically_truant_on_day,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.truant_count_180\\nFROM\\n    (\\n        SELECT\\n            *\\n        FROM\\n            HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS\\n    ) HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS\\nWHERE\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.att_date >= TO_DATE(:entrydate, 'MM/DD/YYYY')\\nORDER BY\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.att_date,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.school,\\n    HISTORICAL_CALCULATIONS.grade_level\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	7	2026-03-13 12:55:14.209451	2026-03-13 19:59:21.700027
19	Migration guide	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Blade → Mac Mini Migration Guide", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Situation", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Source:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Razer Blade running Proxmox → CasaOS VM → Docker containers, with a 24TB external drive (ext4 format)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Destination:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Mac Mini M4 running macOS, OrbStack, headless via Screen Sharing + Tailscale", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Data:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " ~12TB on the ext4 drive (media, configs, app data)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Already done on Mac:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " OrbStack, Homepage dashboard, Tailscale, SMB bridge from CasaOS, Jellyfin test, Dispatcharr, key macOS settings configured", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Priority:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Clean slate — do it right, no rush", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Part 1: The External Drive Strategy", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Problem", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The 24TB drive is formatted as ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "ext4", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (Linux). macOS cannot read ext4 at all. Plugging it directly into the Mac will prompt \\"Initialize\\" (which means wipe). You need a safe migration path.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Recommended Approach: New Drive + Network Copy", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Since you have ~12TB of data and want to do this right, here's the plan:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Step 1 — Buy a new external drive for the Mac Mini", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "A 16TB drive is the sweet spot. It fits your current ~12TB with room to grow, and the price-per-TB is much better than 24TB drives. Some solid options to look at:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "WD Elements / My Book 16TB (USB 3.0, reliable, budget-friendly)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Seagate Expansion 16TB (similar tier)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "If you want faster: a USB-C/Thunderbolt SSD enclosure + a large NVMe, but this gets expensive at 16TB", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "A 16TB HDD external usually runs $200–300. If you'd rather future-proof with another 24TB, those run $350–450.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Step 2 — Format the new drive as APFS on the Mac", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Open ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Disk Utility", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " on the Mac Mini, select the new drive, click ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Erase", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ", and choose:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Format: ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "APFS", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Scheme: ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "GUID Partition Map", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Name it something clean like ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "MediaDrive", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " or ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Storage", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": ". It will mount at ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "/Volumes/MediaDrive", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": ".", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "APFS is the right call because it's native to macOS and the M-series chips, supports snapshots (instant point-in-time backups), is optimized for SSD but works fine on HDD, and has no third-party driver dependency.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Step 3 — Copy data over the network from the Blade", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "You already have the SMB bridge working from CasaOS. Use it to copy everything to the new Mac-local drive. This is the slow part (network speed), but it's the safest because you never touch the original drive's format.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "From Terminal on the Mac Mini:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"text": "# Create your folder structure first\\nmkdir -p /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/Movies\\nmkdir -p /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/TV\\nmkdir -p /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/Music\\nmkdir -p /Volumes/MediaDrive/Downloads\\nmkdir -p /Volumes/MediaDrive/Backups\\n\\n# Use rsync for the copy (resumable, shows progress)\\nrsync -avh --progress /Volumes/Storage24tb/path/to/movies/ /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/Movies/\\nrsync -avh --progress /Volumes/Storage24tb/path/to/tv/ /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/TV/\\nrsync -avh --progress /Volumes/Storage24tb/path/to/music/ /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/Music/\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Why rsync over drag-and-drop: it's resumable if interrupted, shows progress, preserves permissions, and you can re-run it later to catch anything new without re-copying everything.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Speed estimate:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Over gigabit ethernet, expect roughly 100MB/s, so 12TB would take around 33 hours. Over Wi-Fi it could be much slower. If both machines are on the same network with ethernet, this is a solid overnight-and-a-day job. You can break it up across multiple sessions since rsync picks up where it left off.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Step 4 — Verify, then decommission the old drive", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Once everything is copied and your Mac services are running against the local drive, you have options for the old 24TB ext4 drive:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Keep it as-is on the Blade as an archive/backup", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Reformat it as APFS and use it as a second Mac drive (backup or expansion)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Sell it / repurpose it", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Part 2: Folder Structure (The Clean Slate)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "This is your chance to set up a well-organized structure from scratch. Here's a recommended layout:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "On the external drive (", "type": "text"}, {"text": "/Volumes/MediaDrive", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": ")", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": null}, "content": [{"text": "/Volumes/MediaDrive/\\n├── Media/\\n│   ├── Movies/\\n│   ├── TV/\\n│   ├── Music/\\n│   ├── Audiobooks/\\n│   └── IPTV-Recordings/\\n├── Downloads/\\n│   ├── complete/\\n│   └── incomplete/\\n└── Backups/\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "On the Mac's internal SSD (fast storage for configs and databases)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": null}, "content": [{"text": "/Users/david/MyServer/\\n├── homepage/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── jellyfin/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   ├── config/\\n│   └── cache/\\n├── plex/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── sonarr/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── radarr/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── prowlarr/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── qbittorrent/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── dispatcharr/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   └── config/\\n├── proxy/\\n│   ├── docker-compose.yml\\n│   ├── data/\\n│   └── letsencrypt/\\n└── the-docket/\\n    ├── docker-compose.yml\\n    └── ...\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The golden rule:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Configs and databases go on the internal SSD (fast, reliable). Media and large files go on the external drive (big, cheap). This is the same principle from the Blade setup but cleaner.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Part 3: Service Migration Order", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Migrate one service at a time, verify it works, then move to the next. Here's the recommended order, from easiest to most complex:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 1: Foundation (Already Done)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] OrbStack installed", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] Homepage dashboard running", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] Tailscale configured", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] Screen Sharing working", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] SMB bridge to Blade working", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] Jellyfin test (network mount)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] Dispatcharr running", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "[x] macOS energy/sleep settings configured", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 2: Networking & Proxy", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Move your reverse proxy setup to the Mac. This is the gateway for everything else.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Cloudflare DDNS + Nginx Proxy Manager:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": null}, "content": [{"text": "# /Users/david/MyServer/proxy/docker-compose.yml\\nservices:\\n  cloudflare-ddns:\\n    image: favonia/cloudflare-ddns:latest\\n    container_name: cloudflare-ddns\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    environment:\\n      - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE\\n      - DOMAINS=dcplaskett.com,*.dcplaskett.com\\n\\n  npm:\\n    image: 'jc21/nginx-proxy-manager:latest'\\n    container_name: nginx-proxy-manager\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    ports:\\n      - '80:80'\\n      - '443:443'\\n      - '81:81'\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./data:/data\\n      - ./letsencrypt:/etc/letsencrypt\\n    networks:\\n      - proxy_network\\n\\nnetworks:\\n  proxy_network:\\n    name: proxy_network\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Migration notes:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Copy the NPM ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "data", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " and ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "letsencrypt", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " folders from the Blade to preserve your existing proxy hosts and SSL certs", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Update subdomains: drop the ", "type": "text"}, {"text": ".blade", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " suffix (e.g., ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "sonarr.blade.dcplaskett.com", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " → ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "sonarr.dcplaskett.com", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": ")", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Update the DDNS from ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "oznu/cloudflare-ddns", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " to ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "favonia/cloudflare-ddns", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " (lighter, better maintained)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Use a Cloudflare API ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Token", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (scoped) instead of the global API Key for better security", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 3: Download Stack", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "These should go up before the media servers since they feed content in.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "qBittorrent + Gluetun (VPN):", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"text": "# /Users/david/MyServer/qbittorrent/docker-compose.yml\\nservices:\\n  gluetun:\\n    image: qmcgaw/gluetun:latest\\n    container_name: gluetun\\n    cap_add:\\n      - NET_ADMIN\\n    ports:\\n      - 8080:8080  # qBittorrent Web UI\\n    environment:\\n      - VPN_SERVICE_PROVIDER=your_provider\\n      - VPN_TYPE=wireguard\\n      # Add your VPN credentials here\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    networks:\\n      - proxy_network\\n\\n  qbittorrent:\\n    image: lscr.io/linuxserver/qbittorrent:latest\\n    container_name: qbittorrent\\n    network_mode: \\"service:gluetun\\"\\n    environment:\\n      - PUID=1000\\n      - PGID=1000\\n      - TZ=America/Chicago\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./config:/config\\n      - /Volumes/MediaDrive/Downloads:/downloads\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n\\nnetworks:\\n  proxy_network:\\n    external: true\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Prowlarr", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (indexer manager):", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"text": "# /Users/david/MyServer/prowlarr/docker-compose.yml\\nservices:\\n  prowlarr:\\n    image: lscr.io/linuxserver/prowlarr:latest\\n    container_name: prowlarr\\n    environment:\\n      - PUID=1000\\n      - PGID=1000\\n      - TZ=America/Chicago\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./config:/config\\n    ports:\\n      - 9696:9696\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    networks:\\n      - proxy_network\\n\\nnetworks:\\n  proxy_network:\\n    external: true\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 4: The *arr Suite", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Set these up pointing to the new local drive paths.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Sonarr", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (TV):", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"text": "# /Users/david/MyServer/sonarr/docker-compose.yml\\nservices:\\n  sonarr:\\n    image: lscr.io/linuxserver/sonarr:latest\\n    container_name: sonarr\\n    environment:\\n      - PUID=1000\\n      - PGID=1000\\n      - TZ=America/Chicago\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./config:/config\\n      - /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/TV:/tv\\n      - /Volumes/MediaDrive/Downloads:/downloads\\n    ports:\\n      - 8989:8989\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    networks:\\n      - proxy_network\\n\\nnetworks:\\n  proxy_network:\\n    external: true\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Radarr", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (Movies) — same pattern, different port (7878) and ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "/movies", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " path.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Lidarr", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (Music) — same pattern, port 8686, ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "/music", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " path.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "*", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Key migration note for the arr apps:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}, {"text": " Don't try to copy the databases from the Blade. The internal paths will all be wrong. Instead, set up fresh instances and re-add your indexers (via Prowlarr), download client (qBittorrent), and library paths. Then point them at your existing media folders and let them re-scan. This is part of the \\"clean slate\\" approach and avoids path-mapping headaches.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 5: Media Servers", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Plex:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"text": "# /Users/david/MyServer/plex/docker-compose.yml\\nservices:\\n  plex:\\n    image: lscr.io/linuxserver/plex:latest\\n    container_name: plex\\n    network_mode: host\\n    environment:\\n      - PUID=1000\\n      - PGID=1000\\n      - TZ=America/Chicago\\n      - VERSION=docker\\n      - PLEX_CLAIM=your_claim_token\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./config:/config\\n      - /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media:/data/media\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "For Plex, you ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "can", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}, {"text": " migrate the database if you want to preserve watch history, match data, and metadata. Copy the Plex config folder from the Blade, but you'll need to update the library paths in Plex settings after startup.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Jellyfin", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " — you already have this running from the test. Once the local drive is ready, just update the volume mount from ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "/Volumes/Storage24tb", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": " to ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "/Volumes/MediaDrive/Media", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"text": ".", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 6: Music & Other Services", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Navidrome", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (music streaming):", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"text": "services:\\n  navidrome:\\n    image: deluan/navidrome:latest\\n    container_name: navidrome\\n    ports:\\n      - 4533:4533\\n    environment:\\n      - ND_SCANSCHEDULE=1h\\n      - ND_LOGLEVEL=info\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./config:/data\\n      - /Volumes/MediaDrive/Media/Music:/music:ro\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 7: IPTV (The Hard One)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "You've got Dispatcharr running, which is the right foundation. The remaining pieces:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Recording:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Dispatcharr's HDHomeRun emulation into Jellyfin is the most reliable recording path. Point Jellyfin's Live TV tuner at Dispatcharr's HDHomeRun endpoint.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "EPG fix:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Use Dispatcharr to map IPTorrents channels to a 7-day EPG source (like iptv-org's free XMLTV feeds or EPG.best).", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Match tracking:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Use FotMob or LiveSoccerTV apps to get notifications for Spurs/Man Utd/Liverpool matches, then cross-reference the channel in your IPTV lineup.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Phase 8: Productivity & Development", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Docket", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (your Next.js app):", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"text": "# Already have the docker-compose.yml in your project\\n# Just update if needed and deploy on the Mac\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Other services to consider migrating:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Joplin (notes) — or replace with The Docket if it covers your needs", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Actual Budget (if you were running it)", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Part 4: Drive Reliability on macOS", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Preventing Drive Sleep/Unmount", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "macOS is aggressive about sleeping external drives. For a server, this causes stuttering and dropped connections.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "System Settings:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Energy → \\"Put hard disks to sleep when possible\\" → ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "OFF", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Energy → \\"Wake for network access\\" → ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "ON", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (already done)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Energy → \\"Prevent automatic sleeping\\" → ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "ON", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (already done)", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Amphetamine app (free from App Store):", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Install this and create a trigger that keeps the external drive awake. It's the most reliable way to prevent macOS from spinning down a USB drive.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The auto-mount issue:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " If the Mac reboots and the drive isn't mounted on startup, your containers will start with empty data directories. To prevent this, the drive should auto-mount. For a directly-connected USB drive (not a network share), macOS handles this automatically — USB drives mount on boot. This is actually simpler than the SMB auto-mount you were setting up for the Blade bridge.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Handling the SMB Bridge (Temporary)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "While you're still copying data over from the Blade, keep the existing SMB auto-mount setup. Once the data is fully on the local drive and services are migrated, you can remove the autofs configuration:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"text": "# To remove later:\\nsudo nano /etc/auto_master   # Remove the /- auto_smb line\\nsudo rm /etc/auto_smb\\nsudo automount -cv\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Part 5: Docker Path Reference", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "One of the trickiest parts of migration is getting paths right. Here's a quick reference for how paths map in OrbStack:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "What", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Mac Path", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Container Path", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Notes", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Media drive", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwi