6	Other Improvements	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 6, "status": "todo", "taskId": 35, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "When a task is deleted, that task should be removed from the note it is on (if applicable). Was “fixed” but not anymore", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 6, "status": "todo", "taskId": 59, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Look at improving time and date management. Seems to still be off. Curious if it is setting the time of something like midnight for full day things. It is still showing odd dates when scheduling things around. Might also have to do with syncing (NextCloud vs the Docket)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 6, "status": "todo", "taskId": 61, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": false}, "content": [{"text": "Right sidebar have it float over like left on mobile ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 6, "status": "todo", "taskId": 76, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Have the ability to collapse a block (like code)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	2	2026-02-02 00:56:43.927817	2026-03-13 20:00:00.182048
2	Education Tech Idea - edIT	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Idea would be to create a system of tech needs that are simple that are focused on the educational tech needs. Targeting small to mid sized districts with the need for solutions, but nothing overly complex. Think about having various modules that can work independently, but also work together in a smooth flow.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Ticketing system", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Asset tracking", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Knowledge base", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Productivity Suite", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Software inventory? ( probably asset)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Account creation", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "HR toolbox", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "These various products should be able to enhance each other in various ways", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Names", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "edIT - Overall System", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "TickedIT - Ticket System", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "NotedIT - Knowledge base", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "TrackedIT - Asset System", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "PlannedIT - Productivity System", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Need to have a simple yet unified theme throughout. Think about clear and understandable layouts.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Also the workflow should make sense. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The overarching main goal is to have something that is easy to deploy (via Docker) or cloud host. All of the data is siloed within the system.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "We can build a way to pull in students/teachers automatically. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Everything should be built with ease of use first. Do not introduce anything unfamiliar, especially when it comes to UI or design elements.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "We need to build these:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Lean Canvas- get baseline figures down.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Design Statement - think through visual design and elements", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Architecture - Database structure.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Routing Schematic - How things get called ", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Common Workflow pipelines", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Pitch - a one-pager that can help sell the idea to others", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Feedback - Ways we can gather feedback about bad design and broken systems from those that use them. What are the headaches.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Things we can take a deep dive look at:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Jitbit - this is the main ticket system", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I feel like the skeleton of this system is very good. ", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "There is also a lot of power behind some of the actions. We can work on making those easier.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Learn21 - Asset tracking", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "There is a lot of power in this system, but it takes a lot of work to keep that in check.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "We may be able to find ways to help with parts inventory - automatically tying to types of breakage with override.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Confluence - Knowledge base/ Productivity", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Obviously there is a lot of power here. Usually too much.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I’d say we look at this products as a simple way to get help to those that need it fast.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "While there is public facing pages and answers, we would also need the internal documentation to be robust enough.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Leave the complex “strategies” to the productivity suite.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Trello - Productivity", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Card based system for organizing projects.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The system works nicely for tracking projects", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Alternatives to look at:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "These are others around that might also hold some good ideas, as well as pricing ideas.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Incident IQ", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Learn21 Suite", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Atlasian suite ", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	5	2026-01-28 13:05:21.102142	2026-03-01 21:07:27.578001
1	Ticket System	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The general idea is to build out a ticketing system that would work best for our needs. Below is the basic breakdown of what should be implemented in the product:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Base level ticket logic", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Assigning tickets to users", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Auto-assigning based on conditions", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Buckets for tickets to live in", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Web portal for inputting tickets", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Ways to have multiple email addresses assigned to grab and make tickets", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Statuses", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Due Dates", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Merging", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Canned Responses", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Marking comments as solved for better references.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Advanced backend logic", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Pulling in employee and student information", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Able to automatically make suggestions based on documentation and previous tickets", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Student incidents get added to the system as well", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	5	2026-01-27 19:20:45.06401	2026-02-23 13:18:01.191629
14	Interest form	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Get something going in Google Forms", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Here is a comprehensive draft for an interest form that you can easily copy and paste into Google Forms, Typeform, or Microsoft Forms.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "This form is structured to identify your team’s current pain points (the \\"integration tax\\" of using disconnected systems), assess their daily workflow frustrations (like clunky device check-outs or poor search functions), and prioritize the features they actually care about for a lightweight, K-12-focused tool.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"type": "hardBreak"}, {"text": "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------", "type": "text"}, {"type": "hardBreak"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Form Title: Shaping Our Next IT Management Tool", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Description:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "We are exploring the idea of building a streamlined, all-in-one IT Help Desk and Asset Management tool specifically designed for our needs (and districts like ours). To make sure we build something that actually makes your day-to-day work easier, we need to know what is currently slowing you down and what features you’d love to see. Please take 5 minutes to share your thoughts!", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Section 1: Current Headaches & Bottlenecks", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The goal of this section is to figure out where the team is currently wasting the most time.", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "1. What is the most frustrating part of your daily IT workflow? (Select up to 2)", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Jumping between disconnected systems (e.g., separate ticketing, asset tracking, and Google Admin console)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• The device check-in/check-out process is too slow or requires too many clicks", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Lack of accurate, real-time data on who has which device", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Poor search functionality (can't easily find previous tickets, assets, or knowledge base articles)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• End-users (teachers/staff) submitting tickets with missing information", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Other (Please specify): _______", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "2. How much time do you estimate you spend each week manually updating data across different systems (e.g., updating a spreadsheet, then moving an OU in Google Admin, then closing a ticket)?", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 0-2 hours", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 2-5 hours", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 5+ hours", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "3. Think about our device deployment and collection periods (e.g., start and end of the school year). What is the biggest headache during these rushes?", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• [Open-ended text box]", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Section 2: Feature Wishlist", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The goal of this section is to prioritize the \\"must-haves\\" for a Best-of-Suite K-12 platform without the enterprise bloat.", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "4. How valuable would it be to have Help Desk ticketing and Asset Management unified in a single screen? (i.e., Seeing a teacher's ticket and instantly seeing the exact device assigned to them and its repair history)", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 1 - Not important", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 2 - Nice to have", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 3 - Very important", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• 4 - Absolute game-changer", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "5. Please rate the importance of the following integrations for a new tool:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "(Scale: 1 = Unnecessary, 5 = Critical)", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Google Workspace / ChromeOS Sync", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (e.g., auto-syncing device data, locking missing Chromebooks from the ticket screen)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Student Information System (SIS) Sync", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (e.g., automatically updating user accounts when a student enrolls/withdraws)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Mobile App / Barcode Scanning", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " (e.g., using a phone camera to quickly scan and assign devices in the field)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "6. If we could automate ONE manual task for you through this new system, what should it be?", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Auto-routing tickets to specific techs based on location or issue", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Sending automated emails/reminders to users to return loaner devices", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Automatically invoicing parents/students for damaged devices", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Other (Please specify): _______", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Section 3: End-User & Knowledge Base Experience", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The goal of this section is to understand how to improve the experience for teachers and staff submitting requests.", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "7. How often do end-users submit tickets for issues that could have been solved with a simple FAQ or Knowledge Base article?", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Rarely", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Sometimes", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Constantly", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "8. If we build a self-service portal, what features would make teachers/staff actually want to use it? (Select all that apply)", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• A clean, simple layout without overwhelming IT jargon", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• A smart Knowledge Base that suggests answers ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "while", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}, {"text": " they are typing their ticket", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• The ability to easily track the status of their own tickets and assigned devices", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• Other: _______", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Section 4: Open Feedback", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "9. We want to avoid the \\"bloat\\" of big enterprise systems that cost too much and are too hard to use. What is one feature from our current/past systems that you NEVER use and we should completely ignore?", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• [Open-ended text box]", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "10. Do you have any other ideas, features, or wild wishes for this new tool?", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• [Open-ended text box]", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"type": "hardBreak"}, {"text": "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------", "type": "text"}, {"type": "hardBreak"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Why this format works based on the K-12 market:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Addresses the \\"Integration Tax\\":", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " By asking about time spent jumping between systems, you validate the core problem that disparate systems (like Snipe-IT for assets and Spiceworks for tickets) cause headaches.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Focuses on Google/SIS Integration:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " K-12 admins repeatedly note that syncing with Google Admin (to disable Chromebooks or move OUs) and their SIS is the most critical feature to save time.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "• ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Highlights the \\"Bloat\\" Problem:", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " Question 9 is crucial. As you noted earlier, platforms like Incident IQ are great but can be overwhelming and expensive. Finding out what your techs ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "don't", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}, {"text": " want will help you keep your MVP (Minimum Viable Product) lean and focused.", "type": "text"}]}]}	f	5	2026-02-24 15:59:42.954243	2026-02-25 13:10:09.946459
4	Asset Tracking	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Module for the education tech project", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Features:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Incident management from beginning to end", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Automatically import assets from other management systems (Mosyle, ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Google", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ")", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Incidents can be added to the ticket queue", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Have an easy to scan medium available, something like a bar code or QR code that can be used by computers and the phone. ", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Inspiration", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Learn21 (currently used)", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "SnipeIT (was used for some things)", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	5	2026-01-30 16:00:33.832601	2026-02-24 15:59:07.020276
5	Productivity Suite	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Much of the things that happen elsewhere can be bundled into a productivity suite, where individuals can use various tools to manage time and effort. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Features", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Kanban", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Calendar", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Project Management", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Should be able to loop in things like tickets or ongoing repairs", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Reports can be funneled to here", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Create a maintenance system", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Admin view with various facts and pulls", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	5	2026-01-30 20:47:25.960324	2026-02-23 13:17:59.772793
21	Project Arbor	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "A VPS hosted AI persistence project, letting an AI live in a machine and evolve over time. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The first iteration:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "While the AI will evolve over time, so will the tools I provide it so it can learn and grow. The base line setup is there is an ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "agent.py", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "href": "http://agent.py", "class": null, "title": null, "target": "_blank"}}]}, {"text": " script that is set to run on a cron job every hour. This will view a truncated version of the memories.txt, find out basic things about the current time, events, and weather, then add to that memories.txt file. Then, at night, we have a ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "dream.py", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "href": "http://dream.py", "class": null, "title": null, "target": "_blank"}}]}, {"text": " file that will run and “Cement” some of the solid core memories to shape an identity. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I’ll also want to add in some more simple things like messaging and modular scripting to help with the addition of other functionality along the way. Maybe there can be a learning component, where is get more knowledgable about a topic over time, or something like allowing it to write a more freeform journal entry, rather than the small bits.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "We should also have a way to allow it to chose a name for itself.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Key commands", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": null}, "content": [{"text": "source venv/bin/activate\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	9	2026-03-08 14:31:47.43188	2026-03-08 17:40:21.794854
3	Journal	{"type": "doc", "content": []}	f	\N	2026-01-28 14:19:52.367321	2026-01-28 14:19:52.367321
16	Basic Notes	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Tailscale IP = 100.118.30.107", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Command for docker compose", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": null}, "content": [{"text": "docker compose --env-file ~/MyServer/.env up -d", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "This will reference the env file in the main directory.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Notes for VPN (Gluetun and qBit)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "When you recreate the container, ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Tasks", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 16, "status": "todo", "taskId": 73, "due_date": "2026-03-14T15:59:53.141Z", "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Look at VPN connections issue", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 16, "status": "todo", "taskId": 74, "due_date": "2026-03-14T15:59:56.651Z", "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Start getting Arr stack up and running.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 16, "status": "todo", "taskId": 75, "due_date": "2026-03-15T05:00:00.000Z", "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "If ready, get TV started to copy over", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 16, "status": "todo", "taskId": null, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	8	2026-03-05 04:06:50.426145	2026-03-14 22:48:40.433596
8	Knowledge Base	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "This would be a simple system to have set knowledge that can help users solve problems. The primary focus should be around helping those that put in tickets get easy to find help as well as a simple way for technical teams to share that knowledge over.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Rich Text Editor", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Context automation for linking between issues", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Ability to share pages out to the public easily, without having signins?", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Algorithmic matching of tickets to knowledge, gets better over time.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	5	2026-02-03 14:22:28.974826	2026-02-23 13:17:56.498966
9	Data Dashboard	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The Plan", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "It looks like I can leverage several tools to help build out a pretty powerful data visualization suite. It will take some good planning and work to get things going, but once it is going, I think it will be really nice.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The tech used:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "n8n - Automation of various elements and scripts to help the system. Works through noses, making the process simple and clear.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Postgres - SQL database that is very powerful in the long run", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Metabase - The visualization suite. Here is where much of the time and learning will be.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "There will probably be a few other containers added for convenience. (pgAdmin for one)", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "What I’ve got working:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Docker compose file", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Postgres with data pump", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Metabase with database added and a visualization made.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "What that said, there are a few major pieces we need to iron out.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "How to continually get data in Postgres?", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I’m initially leaning towards the API approach, as it just makes a call over, so we are not pushing files around. This generally means more upfront work to get everything flowing, but adding new pieces shouldn’t be too hard.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The other option is the AutoSend approach, which PowerSchool would send a file over to the docker container and the ingest will happen there. This seems fine as well, and once you set something up, adding new pieces shouldn’t be too difficult.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The other question is on the Postgres side, where we would need to create a table and such. I’ve also got pgAdmin running, which is a database management tool, so tossing in a new table shouldn’t be hard.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Whatever the method would be, I would want to make sure that the steps are easily replicable. ", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "How to store the data?", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Initially I’m thinking of making everything siloed, meaning it is all self contained for each large page of visualization. PII should be the first and foremost thought, so linking students might be difficult, unless we are good to use id or dcid.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The far less likely route is to create relational data. I can see this being helpful further down the line, when we want to start linking things together more, but having the initial data be compatible would be important early on. We would need to grab more data than needed initially so we could cover those changes, especially if we are building appending logic like daily attendance.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "How to make charts?", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"type": null, "start": 1, "tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Metabase will be a new tool, and it will have it’s quirks and ways it wants to do things. I’ll definitely need to sit and learn the tool before even really pulling tons of data. If I can get my head around the charting, I can then help plan out the data pulls more successfully.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "I’ll have to dive into documentation and any videos that might be out there.", "type": "text"}]}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "The ultimate goal would be taking the Looker pages we have now, and hopefully enhancing them with this tool.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Initial steps", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 9, "status": "todo", "taskId": 17, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Offer the plan up to Aaron and Pam - This will dictate the projects course.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 9, "status": "todo", "taskId": 19, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Plan out the data pull - need to get the method figured out.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 9, "status": "todo", "taskId": 18, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Start recreating a Looker page - While I pulled daily attendance for 2 weeks to work on initially, we can look at fully replicating some looker pages.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 9, "status": "todo", "taskId": 21, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Work on some styling and get familiar with the layout and some tricks.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "v2Task", "attrs": {"pageId": 9, "status": "todo", "taskId": 64, "due_date": null, "autoFocus": true}, "content": [{"text": "Work out 180 day nastiness", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "How the setup works", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Here is a baseline rundown of how everything works:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Docker", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Docker is a tool that can create a container of services that all exist in the same instance. We can use something called a Docker Compose file to set up all of the configuration of the setup and Docker will do the rest (pull the services, get them talking, etc.). There will be some configuration of connecting things in the services themselves, but for example, to connect Postgres to n8n, you can just use the service name, rather than trying to find out the IP, etc. You can also have the services depend on a certain service to work, so n8n won’t run if Postgres is not.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "n8n", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "n8n is a node-based workflow tool. You can create flows of logic and data to complete simple or complex actions. There can be some limitations to what it can do specifically, but for this use, it should be able to work wonders. For example, I was able to read a csv from the directory, extract the rows, and upsert in Postgres. We can do something similar with the API pull, so we would have a node for pulling, then be able to swing that around into Postgres.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Metabase", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Metabase is a self-hostable data visualization tool. The base level is free and open source, with paid options for cloud hosting and visual upgrades (no customization out of the box). The charting is based about asking “questions”, which you choose data, filters and things to summarize. You can then make different visualizations based on that. There is also filters you can create for the page itself, which will change all the visuals in turn. It looks like you can create public links to the dashboard for easy sharing, and there is a “newsletter” type of scheduled email that can go out with the data as well. The dashboard is pretty easy to set up and move things around, its all simple grid based.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1, "textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Notes for Metabase", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "attrs": {"tight": true}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "Looks like you can cascade various things to help develop more complex pulls. For example, you can get the count of absences for a week, then add a filter for only those 4 or over, then get the count of that per week.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}, "content": [{"text": "When you copy a graph, you actually use the same question and it’s shared over.", "type": "text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "attrs": {"textAlign": null}}]}	f	7	2026-02-10 13:21:07.715252	2026-03-03 19:20:12.30976
